A common and always special sight. So much respect for this animal and the plight  of the coyote as a species, continuing to evolve, adapt and thrive alongside human expansion and destruction. 

Quote from Dan Flores 
Book “Coyote America” 

If one’s argument for civilization holds that wild predators should never roam in broad daylight through the boroughs of America’s largest, loudest, most radically urban metropolis, then, truly, the end of civilization had arrived on paw prints in the snow.

#sonyalpha

I wonder if this leucistic Anna’s hummingbird knows how special he is.

 Leucism is a rare mutation in birds, mammals and reptiles. 
It’s defined as “an abnormal condition of reduced pigmentation affecting various animals (such as birds, mammals, and reptiles) that is marked by overall pale color or patches of reduced coloring and is caused by a genetic mutation which inhibits melanin and other pigments from being deposited in feathers, hair, or skin”
